# API Authentication & Security

## Overview

NEDA provides multiple authentication methods to secure API access. This guide covers authentication mechanisms, security best practices, and implementation examples.

## Authentication Methods

### 1. API Keys

#### Generation
```bash
curl -X POST https://api.neda.ai/v1/auth/apikey \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"name": "MyAppKey", "permissions": ["read", "write"]}'
```

#### Usage
```csharp
var client = new NEDAClient(new NEDAClientOptions
{
    ApiKey = "your-api-key-here",
    BaseUrl = "https://api.neda.ai/v1"
});
```

### 2. OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect

#### Authorization Code Flow
```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Client] --> B[Authorization Endpoint]
    B --> C[User Consent]
    C --> D[Authorization Code]
    D --> E[Token Endpoint]
    E --> F[Access Token]
    F --> G[API Access]
```

#### Configuration
```json
{
  "oauth": {
    "client_id": "your-client-id",
    "client_secret": "your-client-secret",
    "authorization_endpoint": "https://auth.neda.ai/oauth/authorize",
    "token_endpoint": "https://auth.neda.ai/oauth/token",
    "redirect_uri": "https://your-app.com/callback",
    "scopes": ["profile", "email", "api"]
  }
}
```

### 3. JWT Tokens

#### Structure
```json
{
  "header": {
    "alg": "RS256",
    "typ": "JWT"
  },
  "payload": {
    "sub": "user-id",
    "name": "John Doe",
    "iat": 1516239022,
    "exp": 1516242622,
    "scopes": ["api.read", "api.write"]
  }
}
```

#### Validation
```csharp
var tokenHandler = new JwtSecurityTokenHandler();
var validationParameters = new TokenValidationParameters
{
    ValidateIssuer = true,
    ValidIssuer = "https://auth.neda.ai",
    ValidateAudience = true,
    ValidAudience = "api.neda.ai",
    ValidateLifetime = true,
    IssuerSigningKey = new SymmetricSecurityKey(Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(secret))
};
```

## Security Best Practices

### 1. Credential Management
- Never hardcode credentials
- Use environment variables or secure vaults
- Rotate credentials regularly
- Implement credential encryption

### 2. Rate Limiting
```json
{
  "rate_limits": {
    "per_second": 10,
    "per_minute": 100,
    "per_hour": 1000,
    "per_day": 10000
  }
}
```

### 3. Input Validation
```csharp
[HttpPost("execute")]
public async Task<IActionResult> ExecuteCommand([FromBody] CommandRequest request)
{
    // Validate input
    var validator = new CommandRequestValidator();
    var validationResult = await validator.ValidateAsync(request);

    if (!validationResult.IsValid)
    {
        return BadRequest(validationResult.Errors);
    }

    // Process request
    // ...
}
```

### 4. Audit Logging
```csharp
public class AuditMiddleware
{
    private readonly RequestDelegate _next;
    private readonly ILogger<AuditMiddleware> _logger;

    public async Task InvokeAsync(HttpContext context)
    {
        var auditEntry = new AuditEntry
        {
            Timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow,
            UserId = context.User?.FindFirst(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)?.Value,
            Action = $"{context.Request.Method} {context.Request.Path}",
            IpAddress = context.Connection.RemoteIpAddress?.ToString(),
            UserAgent = context.Request.Headers["User-Agent"].ToString()
        };

        // Log audit entry
        await _auditService.LogAsync(auditEntry);

        await _next(context);
    }
}
```

## Error Handling

### Standard Error Response
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "AUTH_001",
    "message": "Invalid API key",
    "details": "The provided API key is invalid or has expired",
    "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
    "request_id": "req_1234567890abcdef"
  }
}
```

### Common Error Codes
| Code | Meaning | Resolution |
|------|---------|------------|
| AUTH_001 | Invalid credentials | Verify API key or token |
| AUTH_002 | Token expired | Refresh token |
| AUTH_003 | Insufficient permissions | Request appropriate scopes |
| AUTH_004 | Rate limit exceeded | Wait and retry |

## Implementation Examples

### Python Example
```python
import requests
from datetime import datetime, timedelta
import jwt

class NEDAClient:
    def __init__(self, api_key, base_url="https://api.neda.ai/v1"):
        self.api_key = api_key
        self.base_url = base_url
        self.session = requests.Session()
        self.session.headers.update({
            "Authorization": f"Bearer {api_key}",
            "Content-Type": "application/json"
        })

    def generate_jwt(self, user_id, private_key):
        payload = {
            "sub": user_id,
            "iat": datetime.utcnow(),
            "exp": datetime.utcnow() + timedelta(hours=1)
        }
        return jwt.encode(payload, private_key, algorithm="RS256")
```

### JavaScript/Node.js Example
```javascript
const axios = require('axios');
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');

class NEDAClient {
    constructor(apiKey, baseUrl = 'https://api.neda.ai/v1') {
        this.client = axios.create({
            baseURL: baseUrl,
            headers: {
                'Authorization': `Bearer ${apiKey}`,
                'Content-Type': 'application/json'
            }
        });
    }

    generateToken(userId, privateKey) {
        return jwt.sign(
            { sub: userId, iat: Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) },
            privateKey,
            { algorithm: 'RS256', expiresIn: '1h' }
        );
    }
}
```

